Sentencas: This work presents the results of a comprehensive study on the impact of the A-site non-stoichiometry of SrxTi0.3Fe0.7O3-d (x = 0.90, 0.95, 1.00, 1.05) ceramics on their physico-chemical properties.
Titulo: Impact of strontium non-stoichiometry of SrxTi0.3Fe0.7O3-d on structural, electrical, and electrochemical properties for potential oxygen electrode of intermediate temperature solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The materials were fabricated by the conventional solid-state reaction method and their structure was determined by X-ray diffractometry, X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy and electron microscopy.
Titulo: Impact of strontium non-stoichiometry of SrxTi0.3Fe0.7O3-d on structural, electrical, and electrochemical properties for potential oxygen electrode of intermediate temperature solid oxide cells

Sentencas: Their sintering and thermal expansion properties were then evaluated.
Titulo: Impact of strontium non-stoichiometry of SrxTi0.3Fe0.7O3-d on structural, electrical, and electrochemical properties for potential oxygen electrode of intermediate temperature solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The electrical properties of the materials were determined by elec-trical conductivity and electrical relaxation measurements (on bulk materials) and by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) studies of symmetrical, CGO-electrolyte based, porous electrodes.
Titulo: Impact of strontium non-stoichiometry of SrxTi0.3Fe0.7O3-d on structural, electrical, and electrochemical properties for potential oxygen electrode of intermediate temperature solid oxide cells

Sentencas: Finally, fuel cell tests with the non-stoichiometric electrodes were evaluated.
Titulo: Impact of strontium non-stoichiometry of SrxTi0.3Fe0.7O3-d on structural, electrical, and electrochemical properties for potential oxygen electrode of intermediate temperature solid oxide cells

Sentencas: To elucidate the electrochemical reaction pathways for oxygen reduction/ evolution reaction, EIS measurements were carried out in different pO2 and were analysed via the distribution of relaxation times method.
Titulo: Impact of strontium non-stoichiometry of SrxTi0.3Fe0.7O3-d on structural, electrical, and electrochemical properties for potential oxygen electrode of intermediate temperature solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The results showed a dependence of materials' properties on the A-site non-stoichiometry, which can be used to fine-tune their properties, e.g. increase the surface exchange rate or decrease the thermal expansion coefficient.(c) 2023
Titulo: Impact of strontium non-stoichiometry of SrxTi0.3Fe0.7O3-d on structural, electrical, and electrochemical properties for potential oxygen electrode of intermediate temperature solid oxide cells
